If you have the Statistics Toolbox, you can use [`pdist2`](https://www.mathworks.com/help/stats/pdist2.html) to compute the distance matrix:

    result = pdist2(array1(:), array2(:)) &lt;= 2;

As noted by [@Adriaan](https://stackoverflow.com/users/5211833/adriaan), this is not efficient for large input sizes. In that case a better approach is a loop with preallocation of the logical matrix output, as in [his answer](https://stackoverflow.com/a/57952662/2586922).

